Sria<br>
Registered User<br>
(1/24/01 3:14:56 pm)<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
 Returns home in mid-day with her husband and picks up the on thier way in. Sitting down on the balcony Sria has her husband read the letter that was left at the door<br>
<br>
Upon hearing &quot;I am glad to hear that you have let The Father back into your heart,&quot; she laughs at such a conclusion<br>
<br>
&quot;Are your kind really so thick sculled, my dear, that they must draw a conclusion from a simple thank you letter?&quot;<br>
<br>
Feels her husband eyeing her with a grin upon his lips<br>
<br>
&quot;No. Tull, I am not serving that wicked god you call Father ever again. Write a letter again for me and have it sent immediatly and delivered into the hands of Shaede, before they get any more foul thoughts in thier heads.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Attention Lady Shaede,<br>
<br>
M'lady, where does this foolish belief that I have invited Your Father into my heart? You are mislead. The letter was ment as a simple thank you to the Harvest, nothing more. <br>
As for your 'test', should should have expected a short delay from one who is blind with what you required of me. I am near finished, you may be glad to know.<br>
<br>
Sria Har`Graef<br>
45th Blind Enchantress of Marr<br>
Subject of Dark and Light<br>
Knights Templar<br>
